My mom's an insomniac.

858
01:22:22,572 --> 01:22:25,284
We better take our car.
There's more room.

859
01:22:26,952 --> 01:22:29,246
Think you can handle a station wagon?

860
01:22:30,332 --> 01:22:33,374
Sure. It's not a stick, is it?

861
01:22:33,460 --> 01:22:35,961
- No.
- Yeah, no problem.

862
01:22:36,213 --> 01:22:39,591
- Will you let me steer?
- Sure.

863
01:22:39,966 --> 01:22:43,220
But maybe we should go.
I heard somethin'. Could be your mom.

864
01:22:43,971 --> 01:22:46,056
Come on in.

865
01:22:56,025 --> 01:23:00,155
I'll go wait in the car.
You guys wait here for my sisters.

866
01:23:56,299 --> 01:24:00,261
These girls are making me crazy.
If I could feel one of'em up just once…

867
01:24:03,891 --> 01:24:05,559
What?

868
01:24:22,953 --> 01:24:26,290
We would never be sure
about the sequence of events.

869
01:24:26,792 --> 01:24:28,877
We argue about it still.

870
01:24:32,005 --> 01:24:35,842
Most likely Bonnie had died while we
were waiting in the living room…

871
01:24:35,926 --> 01:24:38,011
…dreaming of highways.

872
01:24:39,054 --> 01:24:42,225
Mary put her head in the oven
shortly thereafter.

873
01:24:42,975 --> 01:24:47,647
Therese, stuffed with sleeping pills,
was gone by the time we got there.

874
01:24:48,398 --> 01:24:50,233
Lux was the last to go.

875
01:25:00,035 --> 01:25:04,332
